<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="run-v">run <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /rʌn/    美 /rʌn/  </p>
<p>(ran, run)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>跑 (某段距离)；赛跑；(液体) 流动：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sibson ran back upstairs to call 911 from his bedroom.
西布森跑回楼上的卧室拨打911。</p><footer>2012 重庆</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>At age 18, Ben ran his first marathon. 
18岁时，本第一次参加马拉松比赛。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The river was running very slowly. 
河水流得很慢。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(使) 运转；运行；操作：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I think that clock is running a bit slow. 
我觉得那个钟走得有点慢。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He ran the motor to see if it was working. 
他启动发动机看它是否运转正常。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>管理；经营：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When I was young, my parents ran a snack bar in our small town. 
我小的时候，父母在我们的小镇上开了一家小吃店。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>(尤指在美国) 参加竞选：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>run in election 
参加竞选</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>run for president 
竞选总统</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>变成；成为：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We’ve run short of milk. 
我们没牛奶了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="run-across">run across</h3>
<p>1.<strong>跑着穿过；偶然碰见：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He ran across the fields. 
他跑过了田野。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I ran across him at a conference in Milan. 
我在米兰的一次大会上碰到了他。</p></div>

<h3 id="run-after">run after</h3>
<p>1.<strong>追赶；追求：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If you run after two hares, you will catch neither. 
面面俱到，诸事未了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is said that John’s always running after younger women. 
据说约翰总是追求年轻女子。</p></div>

<h3 id="run-away-from">run away (from)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>逃走；逃避：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The thief heard the noise and ran away quickly. 
小偷听到声音，匆忙逃走了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s irresponsible of you to run away from difficulties.
见了困难就躲是不负责的。</p></div>

<h3 id="run-into">run into</h3>
<p>1.<strong>撞上；偶然遇见；遇到 (困难等)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The driver of a large truck, unable to stop in time, ran into our car. 
大卡车司机没能及时停车，撞上了我们的车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I ran into Linda and we went to a pub. 
我遇见琳达，然后我们一起去了酒吧。</p><footer>2008 湖北</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When I first learned to write in English, I ran into many difficulties. 
我刚开始学习用英语写作时，遇到了很多困难。</p></div>

<h3 id="run-out-of">run out (of)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>用完；耗尽：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In the future, care for the environment will become very important as earth’s natural resources run out.
在未来，爱护环境将会很重要，因为地球的资源将濒临枯竭。</p><footer>外研④ – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My car broke down on the way to the beach because it had run out of petrol. 
在去海滩的路上，我的车因为汽油耗尽而抛锚了。</p><footer>北师大⑥ – 16</footer></div>

<h3 id="run-over">run over</h3>
<p>1.<strong>碾过；思考：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To the public’s sadness, she was run over and killed by the bus. 
令公众伤心的是她被公共汽车撞死了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mark’s mind raced, running over all the possibilities. 
马克的脑子飞快地转着，把各种可能都一一作了考虑。</p></div>

<h3 id="run-through">run through</h3>
<p>1.<strong>跑着穿过；把…匆匆过一遍</strong>  </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— OK, I’ve had enough of it. I give up.
— You can’t run away <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ your responsibilities.  （2012 江苏改）  </li>
<li>— I’m still working on my project.
— Oh, you’ll miss the deadline. Time is running <strong><em>_</em></strong>_.  （2008 江苏改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. from  2. out  </p></div>